structure.unit: Crimes, Punishments And Proceedingsin Criminal Cases

law.catch_line: Assault; Intent To Commit Felony; Punishment
law.text: Whoever assaults another with intent to commit a felony shall, if the punishment of such assault is not hereinbefore provided, be punished by imprisonment in the state prison for not more than ten years or by a fine of not more than one thousand dollars and imprisonment in jail for not more than two and one half years.
